poem:
Rage filled flames fuel the fury;
On caged, chilled claims fools do worry;
Trees we once knew; charred wood we now know;
These bombs of new; tarred, nuclear snow.

Blossoming, bursting, beautiful, but only for a season;
 Removed, rotting, regrettable, it's dying is the reason;
 We pick and we admire but we don't think
 It fades to black from a bright and rosy pink

A roses blooms
as it captures the sun's glow;
Vibrant red in the sun's light
Reminder that the day near; 
The rose is surrounded by a garden of life
Awaking to greet a new day;
The garden is full of peace, 
As the rose leads the way to a new day
